body.name: Men's Casual Leather Belt
features: CASUAL TIMELESS DESIGN: Adding a touch of style to your jeans or khakis is now a no-brainer. The belt strap features two rows of stitches on edges, a matte finish harness buckle and a pointed tip that finish off the classic silhouette of the belt.
100% LEATHER: Crafted from genuine leather, this high-quality belt provides you a nice and clean look to complement any outfit. The sleek and smooth leather strap is perfect to finish off any outfit.

DICKIES QUALITY: At Dickies, we take pride in designing belts that are made for your everyday life. From work to family time, we craft sturdy, yet fashionable belts that you can wear anytime and anywhere.
SIZING: Regular and Big & Tall sizes available. Fits from size 30" to 56". For best fit, order a size 2" larger than your waist size. For example, if your waist size is 34", order belt size 36".
body.description: The dickie's brand name is synonymous with work wear, being tough, and built to last. This belt lives up to the dickie's name and adds a bit of flair with the extra stitching.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Actually pretty dern nice!
reviews.reviewText: Well-made belt with large buckle for ease of use. I use them in my Docker casual pants. My only quarrel with them, the leather tends to squeak when pressed. Otherwise, the fit is nice, and the finish is top-notch!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not stiff at all - hope it will hold up
reviews.reviewText: This belt is quite soft and flexible. Seems to be made well, and was the length ordered.I'm replacing a belt that was much stiffer, but lasted a long time. However, it eventually had issues with the holes expanding and nearly ripping (belt too tight, maybe). So, I'm hoping the softness of this belt doesn't translate to easier deformation/elongation of the holes. Time will tell.For the price, this belt seems worth the money spent. Definitely comfortable. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars This belt looks great when new, but...
reviews.reviewText: This belt looked great when new, but as it has worn, the finish seems to degrade and the belt seems not to be made of one piece of leather. It looks to me as if it is split leather and stitched together. The belt holes stretch out and take on a ragged look. For the money, I do not believe you get what is paid for. However, the belt is still in use and I do use it almost exclusively with jeans, so appearance is not of great importance, but again, for the money, I would expect better.

I'm very pleased with this belt. It's a nice thick leather. I like the black buckle. The belt can be worn as a work belt or a good casual belt. I don't think you are going to wear it with a tux, but just about anything else it's good to go.I anticipate this belt holding up my jeans for a long time.
Un gran cinto, materiales premium, alta calidad y buen precio.
I bought this for my fiancé over a year ago. He wears it everyday and it still looks new!

I wear a size 34 pants and had to order a 40" belt to finally fit. I am buckling into the 3rd hole from the end with about 5" of "flap" to tuck into my belt loop.I tried a 36" and the entire belt wasn't even long enough to go around me.
Had the belt for about 3 years for work long days and lots of moving around. It eventually broke but lasted a long time good quality. Will buy a new one.
